Law No. 62/2013, of 26 August. This reform aimed at achieving three primary objectives: to broaden the territorial base of the judicial districts, to set up specialised courts on a national level and to implement a new management model for the court districts. In 2013, 27 courts were converted into ‘proximity sections’. The number of judicial circumscriptions (‘
comarcas
’) was reduced to 23 (previously 231).

                     

                  
 

                     
   
